profile_positions.description:
As of 1 January 2016 my new role is International Manager Reporting and Tax (which was already a huge part of my responisibilities in the past years at the company).

The Reporting and Tax-department takes care of:
- Group reporting and preparation of the consolidated IFRS Financial Statements and Interim Financial Statements;
- First point of contact for the auditors related to the audit of the Basic-Fit group and individual group companies;
- Compliance with IFRS regulations, including the definition, documentation and analysis of position papers and including maintenance of the accounting manual;
- Continuously monitoring the consistency and integrity of the reported data;
- Review of new business transactions, including accounting guidance/interpretation and optimal structuring solutions specific to the accounting result for a variety of topics. Involves understanding the transaction, researching the accounting literature, providing structuring feedback to the business and documenting conclusions once finalized
- Preparation of statutory accounts for all group entities (in all countries);
- Setup and maintenance of Transfer Pricing documentation
- Corporate Income Tax (CIT) declaration, calculation, forecasting & tracking
- Monitoring compliance VAT returns (filings prepared by FSSC)
- First point of contact in case of tax audits (VAT, CIT)
- Monitor thin capitalization rules
- Mergers, restructurings

In the beginning of 2016 the Company and its shareholders have initiated a process to actively explore a new capital structure to support future growth which resulted in an Initial Public Offering (IPO) and listing on Euronext Amsterdam on 10 June 2016. The first half year I was involved in the IPO-process by preparing the IFRS Financial statements 2015 and Interim Financial statements Q1-2016 (which were integrated in the prospectus) and by delivering several reports and information to parties involved in the IPO-process.
